work no matter where she is.  Well, since she, and you, have already
defined your world-specific /eat macros in your sockmload files,
you only need to do two things.  Redefine all your macros as
/eat_specificworldname.  Then /def eat = /eat_${world_name}.
That way, you only have to remember /eat, and it will call the
correct world's /eat-specific macro.  Of course, if you have a
world that doesn't use /eat, then you'll get the warning:
% Macros eat_noteatworld does not exist
But if you try to /eat on that world anyway, then you're alreayd
makinga mistake. :)
	This way, you dont' need a huge /if /elseif* /endif
structure, and it's only a really small change to yoru existing macros.
Oh, and you'd want to take the files out of yoru sockmload /world
definition, and /load them as normal.

