Hooks work with -w.  The macros you give should work.  I suspect that
you either have multiple disconnect hooks sitting around, or your send
hook is competing with some other send hook.  You could even use the -q
on the send hook, since it will still run to completion before tf sends
anything to the mud (and long before the mud could close the
connection).

Remove the -i from your send hook, turn /mecho on, and watch what
happens when you type `quit'.

