OK,

Yes NT is a fully UNICODE environment, the CYGWIN.DLL that this 
relies upon, is not, no double byte character sets are supported.  In 
terms of drawing boxes using the ASCII, don't expect it to work.  
If you want it to work look at ANSI termcodes and character codes,
not ASCII.  

TF running under any flavor of Windows is NOT, let me reiterate this,
**NOT** an MS-DOS program.  Win32 supports a native Win32 Console
that is a full Win32 program and has the Win32 limitations, ie.  ANSI 
NOT ASCII.  TF runs as a Win32 Native application.  Do not confuse this, 
it'll get you in trouble EVERY time.

Yes, Support for the ASCII termcodes could be hacked in, but I'm not 
going to even consider it.

Lastly, the changes in TF to run on NT are nil.  It will compile right 
out of the box.  Some minor changes have been made by Ryan Fitch for
scrollback bugs, mine are for better use of the console and minor 
performance tweaks.  I'm also looking into possible workarounds for bugs
in the cygwin.dll.

Andy





