If you give all the worlds you want it triggered in a certain type,
you can use -T when you define the trigger.  Example:

/addworld -Tfoo world1 1.2.3.4 5000
/addworld -Tfoo world2 6.7.8.9 1000
/addworld -Tboo world3 5.4.6.7 3000

/def -T'foo' -t'*some text*' foo_trig = some command

This trigger will be active in worlds 1 and 2, but not 3.  This is the
only way I know of to specify ("name") worlds for the use of triggers.

