/addworld -T"tiny.mush.sd"      sdru   ruth     xx zen.mudservices.com 1976
/addworld -T"tiny.mush.sye"     sye     charade  xx  203.4.148.2      9999
/addworld -T"tiny.mush.sye"     syefr   friday   xx  203.4.148.2      9999
/addworld -T"tiny.mush.sye"     syerb   rb       xx  203.4.148.2      9999

So each world has a different type.

I discovered by trial and error that macros defined for tiny.mush
still work with tiny.mush.*.  And then I can define macros for type
