you know that /mapcar in lisp.tf does the same as that /doforeach you
posted above, right?
why not just put it in a variable first rather than making a macro?
You can't split it up by positions of 's unless you used getopts() which
seems the way to go.

Try this:
/def doforeach = /if (getopts("c:")) /while ({#}) /eval %{opt_c}%; /shift%;
