> Trouble is, the output from this appears in reverse order.
> Naturally, I tried swapping the order in which /mailsubj
> and /mailmesgcount were called and that didn't work either.
> 
> Any ideas how to get them to appear in the right order and
> why it's going nuts?

/quote normally doesn't actually execute a shell command, just schedules
it.  %ptime seconds later, the command is executed.  Your two processes
run in parallel, and the first is probably slower than the second, which
is why its output comes last.  To make the shell command execute
synchronously (that is, execute NOW, instead of just being scheduled),
use /quote -S.  Also, you can just combine the two commands into one
/quote:

   /def -h'MAIL' mail_hook = \
       /quote -decho % !echo From: `frm | tail -1`; frm -q -S

