You don't need %'s when you're inside an expression (the $[..] part)
So you'd use /set idlewho=$[tolower({P1})]
, and instead of using $[idlewho] for a variable, try using %{idlewho}
instead.

Oh, and one more thing, don't use ^(.*) at the beginning of a regexp, it's
not needed and wastes cpu time. Use %{PL} instead. And don't use /eval
either if you can help it. And use -w in /send in case you change worlds.
And clean up your room and look both ways before crossing the street.

anyway, try this:

/def -mregexp -p1 -t' tells you: ' idleanswer = \
        /set idlewho=$[tolower({PL})]%; \
        /if (idlestatus) \
                /send -w tell %{idlewho} I'm idle at the moment.%; \
        /endif

