> get rid of.. What or rather how should I do this ?

{*} (in glob) only picks up complete words - that is, groups of characters
split by spaces.  With the " before and after the braces, the part that you
are hoping to match the * is no longer a complete word.. therefore \"{*}\"
cannot ever match anything.

I believe I posted the correct solution yesterday, but here it is again
(using regular expressions):

/def -F -mregexp -t'tells you \"(.*[^\"])\"$' name_of_macro = say %P1



