If this is on a diku mud you will get a hell of alot of battle spam, nad
quite few of those lines in the history buffer. So this is not a good
solution. But it should still work, put this in your .tfrc:

/def recallexp = /recall -mregexp %{histsize} '^You receive [0-9]+
experience points[.]$'

then typing /recallexp any time in your session will recall the lines you
want. (default histsize is 1000 lines btw.)

A better solution, one I am using, is to set a global variable called
"exp-cost" in a world hook for a particular world to contain the amount of
exp you need for your next level. Then make a trigger that looks something
like this:

/def -T"diku" -F -mregexp -t'^You have scored ([0-9]+) exp[.]$' t_exp_calc = \
  /repeat -w -0 1 \
    /echo You need a total of %{exp-cost} exp for this level.%%;\
    /echo You require $[{exp-cost}-{P1}] exp to level.

Hope that helps,
