There is no such thing as case insensitive regular expressions. However
you can just check if it is bear or Bear with something like:

/def kil = /send kill $[tolower({1})] %; \
    /let victim=$[strcat("(", toupper(substr({1}, 0, 1)), "|",
        tolower(substr({1}, 0, 1)), ")", tolower(substr({1}, 1)))]%;\
    /def  -mregexp -p2 -t"%{victim} (leaves|ascends|descends) ([a-z]*)\\\\.$$"
        track = ...

So when the argument is "bear" then victim will become "(B|b)ear"
and the trigger will work as usual. I know it looks a bit nasty,
but it sure will work fine ;-)


