OK, I use the following bit for doing spells (It watches for a message
saying the spell wore off, then casts the spell every 6 seconds (or is it
15?) until it sees the successful cast message. The downside is ou have to
write a new version for every spell. If needed, I have a perl script that
spits out exactly what should be added to the file. You should be able to
modify this for your needs.

/def -w<world> -mglob -t'<wearoff message>' \
     wearoff_<world_name>_<skill name> = \
     /recast_<world_name>_<skill name>

/def -w<world> -mglob -t'<succeed message>' \
     succeed_<world_name>_<skill name> = \
     /set spellon_<world_name>_<skill name> 1

/def recast_<world_name>_<skill name> = \
     /set spellon_<world_name>_<skill name> 0 %; \
     /untildone_<world_name>_<skill name>

/def untildone_<world_name>_<skill name> = \
     /if (spellon_<world_name>_<skill name> = 0) \
         /repeat -w<world> -00:00:00 1 cast '<spell name>' %; \
         /repeat -00:00:15 1 /untildone_<world_name>_<skill name> %; \
     /endif


Anything in <>'s should be replaced with something appropriate. Note
multi-word world names/skill names should likely be deliminated by _'s not
spaces in anything that is not send to the MUD. Comments accepted. :)

