In response to the person who wanted a way of repeating the last command,
whether a macro or a mud command, etc:

/def again=\
  /let line=$(/recall -i -- -3) %;\
  /eval -s%sub %line

You can make this a binding (to a key-press like esc-a) if you wish, by:
/def -b'^[a' bind_again=\
  /let line=$(/recall -i -- -2) %;\
  /eval -s%sub %line


(Note the macros are slightly different as typing "/again" counts as another
command (that you don't want to repeat, but the one before it) but a binding
doesn't.)


