Wow this was a hard one to figure out :) An obscure bug. You have
%matching=glob. These are all regexp matches and do not mean anything
useful in glob matches. However, the reason why your cheese and doughnut
triggers still work is that -P (partial hilite) implies -mregexp by the
documentation, so they will be regexp matches, even though you didn't
notice it.

So just put -mregexp in your block_triggers trigger and all will be fine.

