Modified from /require in stdlib.tf

In personal .tfrc:
/set MYLIBDIR ~/priv/lib/Tf
or whatever

In another file (local.tf, for instance, or one that they load
explicitly in startup):
/def -i requiremy = \
        /if /test _loaded_libs !/ "*{%{1}}*"%; /then \
                /load %{MYLIBDIR}/%{1} %;\
        /endif

And we get the advantage of getting to use the standard /~loaded and
_loaded_libs, eg, in file foo.tf:
/~loaded foo.tf

