1) The first trigger has a period, the second doesn't ...
2) If you use /trig, I think it assigns the same priority to the
   macro, so tf will find the matching macro of the highest (here,
   same) priority, then pick a random one of those to execute, so you
   might sometimes get one, sometimes the other.
3) I'd recommend naming your macros as well; expand those out to
   /def -t'etc' name_here = etc
   This way you can also specify the priorities that you want.

