for(i=0;i<100;i++) {
	/openchests %i
}

Now you have a couple choices. Either make the thing recursive:

/def open_em = 
	/openchests %i
	/test ++i
	/if(i<100) {
		/repeat -10 1 /open_em
	}

Or just write up a plain repeat for the number you want

/def open_em =
	/set i=0
	/repeat -10 100 /test openchests(++i)

