TF by itself is not a heavy CPU user, but it is possible for users to
write inefficient triggers, hooks, and macros that will make TF use a
lot of CPU.  One common mistake is using ".*" or "^.*" at the beginning
of a regexp; it is very inefficient, and not necessary.  I can only
suggest having all the users clean up their macros to reduce CPU usage
or risk the wrath of your sysadmin.

