Hi Ken (& everyone),

I was looking over the status bar code, and got to the point of
wanting to be able to easily change the attributes on a particular
field.  I came up with a mod that goes like this:

If the attribute field starts with a %, treat it as a variable
containing the attributes for the field, else treat it as previously.

It allows something like:

/set content_attrs=Cred
/set contents=Whatever
/set status_fields=@more:8 :1 contents:7:%content_attrs :1 ......

And for the attributes of the field to be automagically updated by
just setting the content_attrs field to something else.

It's not as flexible as it could be, nor as efficent - it reevaluates
the attribute variable each time it's needed, rather than just when it
is changed. However, I thought I'd throw it out to you and the mailing
list for comment.

The actual diff file is available at:

ftp://pc24.sr.bham.ac.uk/pub/packages/SOURCES/tf-40a7.status.patch

and for those with RPM based systems, a source RPM, and an i386 binary
RPM are also available (though they also have a patch to increase
history sizes included):

ftp://pc24.sr.bham.ac.uk/pub/packages/SRPMS/tf-40a7-2.src.rpm
ftp://pc24.sr.bham.ac.uk/pub/packages/RPMS/i386/tf-40a7-2.i386.rpm

Cheers,

Mark

