Correct, the shell is irrelevant.  Only the terminal emulator matters.
Termcap/terminfo is also irrelevant, for color.  Very few termcap/terminfo
libraries support color, so tf ignores them and uses the start_color_*
and end_color variables, which by default contain ANSI color codes.
So, to get working wolor, you need an emulator that understands ANSI
color codes, or (less likely) you need to change the color variables to
codes that your emulator understands.  See /help color.

