The internal clock status updates on the minute, and can not be changed.
But you can use a variable, which you set every second:

/repeat -1 2147483647 /set myclock=$[ftime("%I:%M:%S", time())]

And replace the "@clock:5" with "myclock:8" in %status_fields.

/Repeats execute with 0.1s precision, so your clock will never be off
by more than that, compared to the system clock.  (Actually, since you
are probably not using a realtime OS, nothing is guaranteed; but on a
system that isn't too heavily loaded, the previous statement holds.)

