Use variable name space with name mangling.  Ie, if you want an array
called `my_array', make variables `my_array_1' `my_array_2', etc.  You
could track the count in `my_array_size' or similar.


Simple accessor macros might be:

; /array_store <array name> <slot> <value...>
/def array_store =\
    /test ARRAY_%1_%2 := {-2}

; /array_fetch <array name> <slot>
; $[array_fetch(name,slot)]
/def array_fetch =\
    /result ARRAY_%1_%2


You can also do more complex things like multi-dimensional arrays, and
allowing names and slot entries which aren't normally legal variable
name parts.

