/def -p30 -mregexp -h'SEND (^|[^A-Za-z])info([^A-Za-z]|$)' expand_info=\
  /eval %{PL}information%{P2}

The regexp (.*[^A-Za-z]|[A-Za-z] |^) will accept
1. anything, followed by non-alpha, or
2. anything (there is no ^ at the very beginning), one alpha, then space, or
3. nothing

You can collapse 1 and 2 down to just "anything, then non-alpha", if you
don't bind the regexp to the string start with ^.
Likewise for the end of the string, with $.


