CD wrote: 
> I used to use "/egrep whatever /list" but can't in the new version, and can't
> get %| to work with it either :(

The old quote-style version of /egrep is still in %TFLIBDIR/grep.tf
where it always was, and is not compatible with the new tfin-style
defined in %TFLIBDIR/textutil.tf; if you load both files, which one you
get depends on the order of loading and on your setting of %redef.

I recommend using the textutil.tf version.

The %| pipe only works in macro body evaluation, so to use it on the command
line, you must do it in /eval or have %sub > 0.

  /eval /list %| /egrep whatever

Also, in this particular example, /list options may be a better choice:

  /list -mregexp = whatever

(assuming you're searching for "whatever" in macro bodies, not their names).

