The original problem will no longer exist on many terminals in version
40a11.  That version will put the keypad in "application" mode, which
on at least some terminals will make the keypad keys transmit a unique
character sequence instead of a digit character (if Num Lock is on).
For example, on an xterm with the keypad in application mode, a shifted
or numlocked keypad-8 transmits "^[Ox", which is different than the
up-arrow sequence "^[OA".  Whether this will work for you depends on
your terminal emulator.

