...
> I tried using $(/dtime) as an element in the strcat instead of {dtime} but it wouldn't work properly.

Use $$(/dtime).  The evaluation of log_tells changes that to $(/dtime),
which then does the desired thing in the /test expression.

Or even better, change dtime to a function by getting rid of the echo,
and use dtime() intead of $$(/dtime):

  /def dtime = /@test ftime("%%d/%%m/%%Y %%H:%%M", time())

More importantly, you can use tfwrite(tell_handle, ...) instead of
fwrite(tell_file, ...).  Before you start, do:

  /set tell_handle=$[tfopen("~/tf/LOGS/tells", "a")]

