  /if (regmatch("^Party", {*})) /break %; /endif %;\
  <body here>
  caveats: Any highlights will come into affect whether or not "Party" is
    in the string.

4. -p101 -t'^Party' ... (make sure not -F)
   -p100 -t'abc' ...
  caveats: Highlighting will be better than in #4, but you need to choose
    the trigger priorities (and fall-through flags) carefully, so you don't
    block any other triggers or highlights that you don't want to.




