> encounters such a thing (same for the warning %{variable} in expression)?
> I have quite some such "errors" in my code, which is an awful lot of lines,
> and I would prefer to be told about them to step by step get rid of them.

The function syntax warning can not be changed.  But many other warnings,
including the warning for %{var} syntax in an expression, can be enabled
with "/set pedantic=on" (which I highly recommend).

