It might be more simple just to grab a copy that's like your favorite MUD
server, and you can use it for more than running TinyFugue, such as
finding security holes to exploit or to understand how to squeeze more
performance from your character.  If the server of your heart's desire
simply is not available, I know of the MUCK server used by FurryMUCK,
http://www.belfry.com/fuzzball/ is freely available, and setup isn't _too_
bad.  There are likely better servers to use, perhaps even a 'do-nothing'
server just like you want.  But if you are going to go through the
trouble, you may as well duplicate the conditions of where you enjoy
playing and run it as a private test server.  You'll get more milage for
your effort that way.

Also check http://otterspace.com/~nameless/ where we are putting together
a software package for use with FurryMUCK.  The package isn't for Beta
release yet, but it will duplicate software available on NamelessMUCK so
again, you may run a test server and get the inside scoop of the software
running there as the GOD player.  We hope it's a development idea that
catches on with other MU*'s.  The starter database with FuzzballMUCK is
terribly insecure and buggy.

Hope you can access the MU* server of your heart's desire, but if not...
as close as you can get will likely prove more useful than a 'goes
nowhere, does nothing' blank server.

