Use tf's "background", not the shell's.  E.g.,

  /quote -0 -decho !command

You can do whatever shell i/o redirection you want (and you probably do
want to make sure it produces no output), but do NOT use a "&" to make
the shell background the command.  The only difference between this and
/sys is that /sys uses -S, which makes tf wait for the command to
finish, while this uses -0.

