Using the above, it won't be.  That's what the -P (partial) option is for.

The above will match on the regexp 'You glow (red).'.  The '1' option on the
-P applies the partial hilite to the 1st parenthesized subexpression (the
'red').  The 'C' options color just this part white on a red background.

