Actually, the new trigger macro is added immediately (macro deletions
are also applied immediately).  The question is, at what point in the
list?  If the new trigger has higher priority than the calling trigger,
it won't be tested.  If the new trigger has lower priority, it will be
tested.  But, the priority rules (in "/help priority") don't specify
the order of testing of two fall-thru triggers with the same priority,
