"Just have it work" is the whole point of the prompt detection heuristics.
When users connect to an lp-prompting world without defining a type, these
heuristics make it Just Work for them.  But, as you say, it should also
Just Work for non-prompting worlds; the heuristics which used to favor
non-prompting worlds have gotten too agressive.

