What type did you use?  You probably should use "tiny" or "tiny.<something>".
"tiny" and blank are treated identically, with two exceptions:

* A "tiny" world automatically sets lp=0 when you fg it; an untyped world
  leaves lp alone.  This doesn't matter if you never set lp=1.

* A "tiny" world is not subject to the type detection heuristics.

