	SOCKS doesn't use the proxy_* variables internal to TF.  Those
are used strictly for dealing with a telnet proxy.  SOCKS is something
else entirely.  When compiled with SOCKS, TF makes all the usual 
socket calls to equivalent calls in teh SOCKS library.  The SOCKS
library looks for its own configuration file, either /etc/socks.conf
for SOCKS4 or /etc/libsocks5.conf for SOCKS5, and then does its 
own thing.  
	If TF sees proxy_host has a value, it will attempt to use it
(basically defaulting to using a telnet proxy).  If you really want to
use SOCKS, you have to /unset proxy_host and proxy_port.  This way
TF will attempt a 'normal' connection, but the SOCKS library will take
over onthe socket-call level and handle the proxy-ing for you.

-Mike

