Hi,

I've just upgraded my PC from FreeBSD 2.2.5 to FreeBSD 3.0, and
an unfortunate result was that my trusty old tinyfugue (version
3.5 alpha 16) stopped working due to shared library changes.

Not too worried, I installed tf 4.0 beta 2 which was with
the packages for FreeBSD 3.0. The result was not a resounding
success.

After a couple of wasted hours trying to figure out what
I needed to change/add/remove from my .tfrc to get it
to work, I gave up and deleted 4.0 beta 2. After much
rummaging around I eventually located the 3.5a16 source
and recompiling that I'm now happy again.

However, it would be nice to be able to use the latest
version of tinyfugue, so I'm wondering if anyone has any
ideas on how to configure 4.0b2 so that it behaves the
way 3.5a16 does?

The sorts of problems I'm experiencing in 4.0b2 are:

* colour support is erratic. 

Sometimes colour works, sometimes it doesn't. Mostly it
seems it doesn't, especially if the colour codes are at
the start of a line. (ANSI codes). If I set emulation=raw
rather than emulation=ansi_attr then the colour codes 
work but eventually the screen screws up in visual=on 
mode. (In 3.5a16 it works flawlessly with ansi_attr.)
 
I've tried various settings of the TERM environment
variable, ANSI, vt220, vt100, xterm, xterm-color etc
but nothing seems to help (TERM=xterm works for 3.5a16).

The xterm it's running in is an X11R6 xterm, as supplied
with Xfree86 3.3.2 for FreeBSD 3.0.


* automatic login doesn't work

3.5a16 connects and logs into my lpp type worlds fine.
4.0b2 never sends the login character name and 
password.


* worlds go into the background when you connect

In 3.5a16, I connect to a world and it stays in the
foreground. In 4.0b2 it goes into the background and
stays there until I type /fg. I've tried setting
auto_fg=on and bg_output=on in .tfrc but it doesn't
seem to have any effect.


* local echo defaults to off

In 3.5a16, the local echo in the command window stays
on unless the mud sends WILL ECHO (which it does to
disable local echo for password entry). In 4.0b2 the
local echo in the command window seems to switch off
as soon as you connect to a world. It doesn't come
back until the mud sends WONT ECHO after password
entry, or you enable it yourself. This means you
can't see what you are typing as you log in. I can't
find a way to turn off this extra echo.



* commands echo to the world window

In 4.0b2, commands entered in the command window are
echoed in the world window when you press enter, even
if local echo is off. This means when you enter a
password with local echo turned off by the mud, it
becomes visible in the world window when you press enter.


Does anyone have any suggestions as to how I can
fix these problems? The vital one is colour support as
colour coding is important on my mud. The other three
are more annoying than anything else. 

On the other hand, should I just stick with 3.5a16 since
it seems to work fine? 

Any thoughts appreciated,

