Since tf 4.0a9 a MAILPATH env variable has been supported, for multiple
mailboxes.  This uses a colon-separated list.  The alternate syntax we
have uses this, but each element may be a filename, followed by a
question-mark, followed by explanatory text, eg:
 /var/mail/someone:/home/someone/Mail/tinyfugue?Funky new mail in $_!
which becomes more useful with a half-dozen boxes.

If someone knows just how common this is, I'd be interested to hear,
thanks.

The current code is towards the end of stdlib.tf.  This snippet can be
user-included later.

/eval /if (MAILPATH !~ "") \
    /let _hd=%; \
    /let _tl=%{MAILPATH}%; \
    /while (regmatch("^([^?:]+)(\\?[^:]+)?:?", {_tl}))%; \
	/let _hd=%{_hd} %{P1}%; \
	/let _tl=%{PR}%; \
    /done%; \
    /set TFMAILPATH=%{_hd}%; \
/endif

