To perform cursor movment, an application (tf) must, according to the
termcap api, use the termcap "ti" and "te" codes; on some terminals,
cursor movement just won't work without them.  Unfortunately for tf
users, many termcap databases have an entry for xterm which has "ti"
and "te" codes that switch to the alternate screen, which has no
scrollback.

If TERM is "xterm", tf will ignore termcap's "te" and "te" codes so
xterm scrollback works, but for any other value of TERM tf will honor
them.  Perhaps a future version of tf will have an option to ignore
them independant of the value of TERM.

