According to a recent discussion on this list, yes. Consider the
following:

/def -F -ag -msimple -t'Caelum tests' foo = \
  /def -F -p2 -n1 -mglob -t'*' bar = \
    /if ({*} =~ "") \
      /def -p1 -n1 -ag -msimple -t'' baz%%;\
    /endif

'bar' and 'baz' essentially operate on the same line, due to 'bar' having
a higher priority and being fallthrough. So it checks if the line is
empty, and if so automatically generates a gag to remove it.

